'''Libia Grueso''' is a social worker and civil rights activist from [[Buenaventura, Colombia]], fighting for civil rights of Afro-Colombian communities. 

She is also co-founder of the ''Process of Black Communities'' (PCN). She managed to secure more than 24,000&nbsp;km² in territorial rights for the country's black rural communities, and she has been focused on protecting Colombia's Pacific rainforest. Libia Grueso received the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2004.<ref name="goldman">Goldman Environmental Prize: [http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/106 Libia Grueso] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071204051355/http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/106 |date=2007-12-04 }} (Retrieved on November 30, 2007)</ref>

